描述性统计

统计方法概览

峰态：表征概率密度分布曲线在平均值处峰值高低的特征数。直观看来，峰度反映了尾部的厚度。正态分布的峰度为3，小于3则说明更扁平一些。
偏态：是指非对称分布的偏斜状态。换句话说，就是指统计总体当中的变量值分别落在众数（M0）的左右两边，呈非对称性分布。为正表示偏右。

# summary没有提供 skew偏态，kurtosis峰态
mystats <- function(x, na.omit = FALSE) {
  if (na.omit)
    x <- x[!is.na(x)]
  m <- mean(x)
  n <- length(x)
  s <- sd(x)
  skew <- sum((x-m)^3/s^3)/n
  kurt <- sum((x-m)^4/s^4)/n - 3
  return(c(n = n, mean = m, stdev = s, skew = skew, kurtosis = kurt))
}

相关资料1
相关资料2

mytable1 <- xtabs(~Treatment+Improved, data=Arthritis)
mytable2 <- xtabs(~Improved+Sex, data=Arthritis)

chisq.test(mytable1)
## 
##  Pearson's Chi-squared test
## 
## data:  mytable1
## X-squared = 13.055, df = 2, p-value = 0.001463
chisq.test(mytable2)
## Warning in chisq.test(mytable2): Chi-squared approximation may be incorrect
## 
##  Pearson's Chi-squared test
## 
## data:  mytable2
## X-squared = 4.8407, df = 2, p-value = 0.08889
fisher.test(mytable1)
## 
##  Fisher's Exact Test for Count Data
## 
## data:  mytable1
## p-value = 0.001393
## alternative hypothesis: two.sided
fisher.test(mytable2)
## 
##  Fisher's Exact Test for Count Data
## 
## data:  mytable2
## p-value = 0.1094
## alternative hypothesis: two.sided
# 在Sex的每个level，Treatment和Improved都是相互独立的
mytable <- xtabs(~Treatment+Improved+Sex, data=Arthritis)
mantelhaen.test(mytable)
## 
##  Cochran-Mantel-Haenszel test
## 
## data:  mytable
## Cochran-Mantel-Haenszel M^2 = 14.632, df = 2, p-value = 0.0006647

从上可以看出，第一个 p （p < 0.1）值较小，所以我们拒绝二者独立这样的假设。

将 table 转化成原始数据

table2flat <- function(mytable) {
  df <- as.data.frame(mytable)
  rows <- dim(df)[1]
  cols <- dim(df)[2]
  x <- NULL
  for (i in 1:rows) {
    for (j in 1:(mytable$Freq)[i]) {
      row <- df[i, c(1:(cols-1))]
      x <- rbind(x, row)
    }
  }
  row.names(x) <- c(1:(dim(x)[1]))
  return(x)
}

treatment <- rep(c("Placebo", "Treated"), times=3)
improved <- rep(c("None", "Some", "Marked"), each=2)
Freq <- c(29,13,7,17,7,21)
(mytable <- data.frame(treatment = treatment, improved = improved, Freq = Freq))
##   treatment improved Freq
## 1   Placebo     None   29
## 2   Treated     None   13

mydata <- table2flat(mytable)

t 检验

t 检验常用来进行两组之间的比较，可用来回答如下问题： 1. 患者在使用了新药后是不是比使用原来的药有了更好的提升？ 2. 两个教学手段哪个更有效率？

独立性 t 检验

library(MASS)
t.test(Prob ~ So, data = UScrime)
## 
##  Welch Two Sample t-test
## 
## data:  Prob by So
## t = -3.8954, df = 24.925, p-value = 0.0006506
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  -0.03852569 -0.01187439
## sample estimates:
## mean in group 0 mean in group 1 
##      0.03851265      0.06371269

因为 p < .001 所以我们可以拒绝掉：南部州和非南部州有相同的坐牢概率这个假设。

非独立性 t 检验

sapply(UScrime[c("U1","U2")], function(x)(c(mean=mean(x),sd=sd(x))))
##            U1       U2
## mean 95.46809 33.97872
## sd   18.02878  8.44545
with(UScrime, t.test(U1, U2, paired=TRUE))
## 
##  Paired t-test
## 
## data:  U1 and U2
## t = 32.407, df = 46, p-value < 2.2e-16
## alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is not equal to 0
## 95 percent confidence interval:
##  57.67003 65.30870
## sample estimates:
## mean of the differences 
##                61.48936

拒绝原假设（不同年龄段有相同的坐牢率），即年轻人比中年人更容易坐牢。

非参数检验

比较两个组

如果两个组是独立的，我们可以用 Wilcoxon rank sum test（Mann–Whitney U test），来评估观测值是不是都是从相同的概率分布中采样出来的（例如：在A群人中拿到高分的概率是不是比B群要高）。

with(UScrime, by(Prob, So, median))
## So: 0
## [1] 0.038201
## -------------------------------------------------------- 
## So: 1
## [1] 0.055552
wilcox.test(Prob ~ So, data=UScrime)
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum test
## 
## data:  Prob by So
## W = 81, p-value = 8.488e-05
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0

同样我们还是以 p < 0.001 拒绝掉原假设。

sapply(UScrime[c("U1","U2")], median)
## U1 U2 
## 92 34
with(UScrime, wilcox.test(U1, U2, paired=TRUE))
## Warning in wilcox.test.default(U1, U2, paired = TRUE): cannot compute exact
## p-value with ties
## 
##  Wilcoxon signed rank test with continuity correction
## 
## data:  U1 and U2
## V = 1128, p-value = 2.464e-09
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0

以上我们可以看到非参数检验和 t 检验得到了相同结论。

比较更多组

states <- as.data.frame(cbind(state.region, state.x77))
kruskal.test(Illiteracy ~ state.region, data=states)
## 
##  Kruskal-Wallis rank sum test
## 
## data:  Illiteracy by state.region
## Kruskal-Wallis chi-squared = 22.672, df = 3, p-value = 4.726e-05
plot(state.region, state.x77[,3])

显著性检验显示出该国的四个区域，文盲率并不相同，虽然我们可以拒绝原假设，因为 region 有多个，我们并不能判断出哪些 region 是与其它显著不同的。为了回答这样一个问题，我们可以每次挑出两个组来使用 Mann–Whitney U test，当然一种更好的方法是同时进行多组比较。

class <- state.region
var <- state.x77[,c("Illiteracy")]
mydata <- as.data.frame(cbind(class, var))
rm(class, var)
# library(npmc)
# summary(npmc(mydata), type="BF")
aggregate(mydata, by=list(mydata$class), median)
##   Group.1 class  var
## 1       1     1 1.10
## 2       2     2 1.75
## 3       3     3 0.70
## 4       4     4 0.60
